<TITLE>inspect.htm</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="BK11.GIF">
<IMG SRC="oiscredb.gif" HEIGHT="100" WIDTH="250">

<H1>Inspection Staff</H1>


<H2><IMG SRC="BOB.GIF" HEIGHT="75" WIDTH="70" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0">Bob Geiger - Chief Inspector</H2>
<P>Bob has been with the office since 1979 and has served as a field inspector, auditor, and chief
inspector.  Bob has a B.S. degree in Agriculture and a M.S. in Public Policy and Public
Adminsitration from Purdue.</P>

<H2><IMG SRC="Joyse.GIF" HEIGHT="75" WIDTH="70" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0">Joyse Banister - Inspector</H2>
<P>Joyse has been with the office since spring of 1995.  Joyse has a BS in Animal Sciences from Purdue.
Her district is the southeast part of Indiana from Indianapolis to the Ohio River.</P>

<H2><IMG SRC="TIM.GIF" HEIGHT="75" WIDTH="70" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0">Tim Emerick - Inspector</H2>
<P>Tim has a B.S. degree from Purdue University in Animal Sciences.  Before coming to the Indiana
State Chemist, Tim worked extensively in the school of Veternary Medicine.  Tim joined our staff in the summer of 1995
and covers the West-Central part of Indiana.</P>

<H2><IMG SRC="VINCE.GIF" HEIGHT="75" WIDTH="70" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0">Vince Glose - Inspector</H2>
<P>Vince covers the Northeast section of Indiana.  Vince earned a B.S. degree in Agriculture from Purdue.  Before joining
our staff in 1989, Vince was actively engaged in commercial livestock and crop farming.</P>

<H2><IMG SRC="NEFF.GIF" HEIGHT="75" WIDTH="70" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0">Ken Neff - Inspector</H2>
<P>Ken has served as an inspector in various parts of Indiana since 1982.  Ken currently covers the East-Central
region of Indiana.  Ken also graduated from Purdue with a B.S. in Agriculture.</P>

<H2>Julie Stephens - Inspector</H2>
<P>Julies covers the Southwest part of Indiana from Terre Haute to Evansville.  Julie joined our staff
in 1994.  She has a B.S. degree in Animal Sciences from the University of Illinois.  Before joining our
staff she was engaged in livestock and grain production on the family farm.</P>









</BODY>
