<HTML><HEAD>
<CENTER>
<TITLE>Geospace - The Austrian Satellite Remote Sensing Company</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY background="/images/logoemb.gif"> 
<A HREF="/geospace/hmge.html"><IMG SRC="/images/logosmall.gif"></a>   
<H2><I> GEOSPACE</I> - The Austrian Satellite Remote Sensing Company</H2>
<HR>
<I> There is a <A HREF="/geospace/profil_g.html">German Version</A> of this text available 
</CENTER>
</I><HR><P>GEOSPACE is an institute for applicated research in, and practical application of<BR><BR>

<dd> <IMG
SRC="/myicons/red_ball.gif"><STRONG>Satellite Remote Sensing</STRONG> and<BR>
<dd> <IMG
SRC="/myicons/red_ball.gif"><STRONG>Geo Information Systems.</STRONG>

<P>The company was established in 1986 in Bad Ischl/Austria when Satellite Remote Sensing was internationally commercialized (SPOT Image, EOSAT, etc).  1994 Geospace moved to the Technology Center in Salzburg.
<P>
Geospace's purpose is to offer<BR><BR>
<dd> <IMG
SRC="/myicons/red_ball.gif"><STRONG>Remote Sensing Services</STRONG> to all kind of users and to create<BR> 
<dd> <IMG
SRC="/myicons/red_ball.gif"><STRONG>Remote Sensing Products</STRONG>
 for the general market.
<BR><BR>
<HR>
<P><H2><STRONG>Fact Sheet</STRONG></h2>
<P>	 
<STRONG>The company:</STRONG>
<dd>GEOSPACE GmbH
<P>
<STRONG>Operational institute:</STRONG>
<dd>A-5020 Salzburg, Jakob-Haringer-Str. 1
<dd>Tel: +43-662-458115
<dd>Fax: +43-662-4581154
<dd>e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:beckel@geospace.co.at">beckel@geospace.co.at</A> <BR><P>
<STRONG>Manager:</STRONG>			
<dd>Univ. Doz. Dr. Lothar Beckel
<P> 
<STRONG>Affiliations:</STRONG>
<dd>Shareholder of Austrian Space Agency (ASA), Vienna<BR>
<P>
<STRONG>Field of Work</STRONG>
<dd>Remote Sensing and Geographic Information Systems - 
<A HREF="/geospace/produc_e.html">products and services</A> <BR>
<P>
<STRONG>Equipment</STRONG>
<dd>Equipped for all types of image processing, data evaluation and 
<dd>carthographic and photographic works<br><p>
<STRONG><A HREF="/geospace/proima_e.html">Archive:</STRONG></a>
<UL>
Geospace holds a large archive on all types of satellite image data, so for instance<br> 
<i><LI>1 full coverage on CCT's of Austria with: Landsat MSS 1974/75,
<LI>2 full coverages Landsat TM - mid 80ies and beginning 90ies; 
<LI>1 full coverage of Austria with SPOT-panchromatic and SPOT XS, late 80ies; 
<LI>full coverage of Germany with LANDSAT TM data, beginning 90ies.
<LI>Great archive on European data and selected imagery from all the other continents.
</ul>
<HR>
