<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Satellitenbildatlas &Ouml;sterreich</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win16; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/logoemb.gif">

<CENTER><P><!--
Author:	HTMLed User
Date:	September 14, 1995
--><A HREF="/geospace/hmge.html"><IMG SRC="/images/logosmall.gif" ></A><BR>
<BR>
<!--   Text fuer OE3-Atlas:  --></P></CENTER>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><A NAME="syrien"></A>The extraordinary view of Syria:</H3>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Space Image Atlas - Syria</H2>

<P>This Space Image Atlas of Syria covers the whole country with excitingly
colourful satellite image maps at the scale of 1:200 000. Selected views
are presented at the scale of 1:50 000. The book is bilingual - Arabic
and English. If you have not already visited this country you will want
to after you have explored its beatuiful landscape in this wonderful book.
All maps are presented in a cartographic frame. Text and arial photographs
give detailed information. 
<HR>You can order the book &quot;Space Image Atlas - Syria&quot; directly
via <A HREF="mailto:beckel@geospace.co.at">e-mail</A> at the price of <B>ATS
698,-</B> (excl. shipping costs and packaging). <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<center>
<A NAME="globch"></A><IMG SRC="/myicons/em_spectrum.gif" ><BR>
</center>
</P>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>A documentation of our
changing world:</FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Global Change Atlas</H2>

<P><IMG SRC="/images/globch.gif" HSPACE=20  ALIGN=LEFT> Our world is constantly
changing. This Global Change Atlas is describing the natural changes as
well as those caused by man in a fascinating way. Thematic maps and satellite
images are presenting actual themes such as earthquakes, vulcanoes, flooding,
hurricans, desertification as well as water an air pollution. The interaction
of the different natural systems (climate, wind, oceans, etc.) with the
human society is described in a way that makes us understand the fragility
of our global envrionment. The atlas is available in German only. . 
<HR>You can order the &quot;Global Change Atlas&quot; via <A HREF="mailto:beckel@geospace.co.at">e-mail</A>
at the price of <B>ATS</B>&nbsp;<B>569,- (DM 78,-)</B> (excl. shipping
costs and packaging). </P>

<CENTER><P><BR clear=left>
<BR>
<A NAME="kal97"></A><IMG SRC="/myicons/em_spectrum.gif" ><BR>
</P></CENTER>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Just on time for the end of the year:</H3>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>&quot;Die Erde aus dem Weltall&quot; - calender 1997</H2>

<P>12 extraordinary, large (60 x 50 cm) satellite images in wonderful colours
are presenting you a beautiful part of our world each month. Impressive
landscapes from New York, the Grand Canon to the Andes and Sibiria are
shown from the &quot;space perspective&quot;. 
<HR>You can order the &quot;Die Erde aus dem Weltall&quot; via <A HREF="mailto:beckel@geospace.co.at">e-mail</A>
at the price of <B>ATS 569,- (DM 78,-)</B> (excl. shipping costs and packaging).
</P>
<center>
<p><IMG SRC="/myicons/em_spectrum.gif" ><BR>
</center>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><A NAME="oe3atlas"></A>At the Austrian Millennium we present:</H3>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>&Ouml;sterreich - Ein Portr&auml;t in Luft- und Satellitenbildern</H2>
<P>From the &quot;Bodensee&quot; to the &quot;Neusiedlersee&quot; 74 of
the most beautiful Austrian landscapes have been selected to be presented
in extraordinary high resolution satellite images. For the first time the
ground resolution of the images is 10 m, so that even single standing houses,
streets and rivers are seen on these images. New printing techniques also
contribute to the exceptional quality of the images. Illustrated with many
arial photographs and explained by a professional geographer, these satellite
images give an a new exiting view of the beautiful Austrian landscape at
the end of its first Millenium. The book is available in German only. 
<HR>You can order the book &quot;&Ouml;sterreich - Ein Portr&auml;t in
Luft- und Satellitenbildern&quot; directly via <A HREF="mailto:beckel@geospace.co.at">e-mail</A>
at the price of ATS <B>498,-</B> (excl. shipping costs and packaging).
</P>
<br>
<p><A NAME="oe1atlas"></A>
<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="/myicons/em_spectrum.gif" ><BR>
<p><B>In a new edition and cheaper than ever before</B>:
</P></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Satellitenbildatlas &Ouml;sterreich</H2>

<P><IMG SRC="/images/atlas1.gif" HSPACE=20  ALIGN=LEFT>
The Satellite Image Atlas of Austria is covering the whole country with
maps at the scale of 1:200 000. Additionally most of the province capitals and
additionally selected landscapes are shown
in the scale of 1:50 000, revealing details as small as single houses and
roads.<BR clear=all>

<p><HR>You can order the Satellitenbildatlas &Ouml;sterreich via <A HREF="mailto:beckel@geospace.co.at">e-mail</A>
at the price of<B> ATS</B> <B>363,-</B> (excl. shipping costs and packaging)
<BR>
