<HEAD>
<CENTER>
<TITLE>GEOSPACE Forest Atlas</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="/images/logoemb.gif">
<A HREF="/geospace/hmge.html"><IMG SRC="/images/logosmall.gif"></a>    
<center><H1><font color="#115500">
Satellite Remote Sensing Forest Atlas of Europe </font></h1>
</center>
<br><p>
<img align=left hspace=30 src="/images/waldatlg.gif">
</enter><b>Lothar Beckel: 
<br>Satellite Remote Sensing Forest Atlas of Europe</b>
<br>Justus Perthes Verlag Gotha GmbH, Gotha 1995
<br>ISBN 3-623-00035-3.</center><br>
The goal of this book is to show the far reaching potential of satellite
remote sensing when applied to forests. The first part of the atlas contains a short introduction in satellite remote 
sensing and digital image processing for forest applications. In the second part
a large number of thematic satellite image maps gives an overview of the 
distribution and condition of the european forests. Finally each european
state is treated with respect to typical problems of its forests and the application
of adequate satellite remote sensing methods.

<br clear=left><br>
<center><img src="/myicons/forest.gif">
