<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Oesterreichisches Fernerkundungs-Datenzentrum</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win16; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/ofd12b.gif">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="/images/ofd25.gif" > </P></CENTER>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Austrian Remote Sensing Data Center (OFD)</H1>

<CENTER><P><I>(Zur <A HREF="/ofd/hmofd.html">deutschen Version</A>)</I> 
</CENTER>
<P>As the<B> first satellite images</B> where published, people where as
equally as overwhelmed as with the first photos: <B>the</B> <B>Earth as
seen from space</B> - a perspective that has changed the human way of thinking.
After 20 years of development <B>satellite
image data </B>is now used as increasingly important information 
source by <B>decision
makers worldwide</B> to formulate their strategies on the <B>sustainable
use of the resources of our Earth</B>. Satellite image data is applied
in the areas of environmental monitoring, agriculture, forestry, management
of resources, geology, cartography and many more.</P>

<P>To make the satellite image technology more easily available to Austrian
users the <B>OFD - Austrian Remote Sensing Data Center</B> was established
by <B><A HREF="http://geospace.co.at">GEOSPACE GmbH</A></B> (distributor
of satellite image data in Austria since 1986) and the <B>Techno-Z Salzburg
Research Association</B> in 1995.<BR>
<p>The<B> OFD</B> is <B>consulting about all questions of satellite remote
sensing</B>, advising on the <B>use of the different data types</B> and<B>
ordering and delivering the data</B> for the customer. Therefore the <B>OFD
</B>is the link between the <b>worldwide data providers</b>
and the <b>Austrian user community</B>. In a customer
data base the <B>OFD</B> collects the requirements of users
and on one hand informs them about news in their special interest area
and on the other hand informs the satellite industry about specific requirements
of the potential customers.</P>

<P>The<B> future</B> of Earth Observation via satellite has just
begun. The possibility to aquire<B> data with 1 m ground resolution</B>
in the next years will lead this technology into a new dimension. The <B>OFD
- Austrian Remote Sensing Data Center</B> will <B>support Austrian organisations</B>
in <B>using this new technology for their purposes</B> by offering <B>tailor
made services</B>. <BR>

<P>
<HR></P>

<UL>
<H4><IMG SRC="/myicons/gold.gif" ><A HREF="/ofd/ofdserve.html"> OFD - Services</A></H4>

<H4><IMG SRC="/myicons/gold.gif" ><A HREF="/ofd/newsofd_e.html"> OFD -
NEWS</A></H4>

<H4><IMG SRC="/myicons/gold.gif" ><A HREF="/ofd/inh_e.html"> OFD - Information
on Available Satellite Image Data</A></H4>

<H4><IMG SRC="/myicons/gold.gif" ><A HREF="/ofd/data_e.html"> OFD - Remote
Sensing Data Search Request</A></H4>

<H4><IMG SRC="/myicons/gold.gif" ><A HREF="mailto: satdata@ofd.ac.at">
OFD - Remote Sensing Data Order via e-mail</A></H4>
</UL>

<p><hr>
<center>
<p><B><I>We hope, that you find our web pages an interesting information
source. Please contact us for further details via email:</I></B> <B><A
HREF="mailto:satdata@ofd.ac.at">satdata@ofd.ac.at</A></B></P>

<P>
<HR><I>&copy; by &Ouml;sterreichisches Fernerkundungs-Datenzentrum / <A HREF="mailto:satdata@ofd.ac.at">satdata@ofd.ac.at</A>
<BR>
last modified 96/11/20 </I>
<HR></P></CENTER>

