<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE></TITLE>
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Romana Erlacher">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win16; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/ofd12b.gif">
<CENTER><P><A HREF="/ofd/hmofd_e.html"><IMG SRC="/images/ofd12.gif"></A></P></CENTER>

<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">LANDSAT</FONT></H1>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<P>The first satellite of the<B> American Landsat</B> (Landsat 1) <B>mission
</B>was launched in 1972. Today Landsat 5 circles the Earth in approximately
100 minutes at an altitude of 705 km. The whole surface is covered in 16
days which allows a revisit capability of a certain area within<B> 16 days</B>.
Landsat 5 is equipped with two optical sensors: </P>

<UL>
<LI>the Multispectral Scanner (MSS) delivers data in four spectral channels
</LI>

<LI>the Thematic Mapper (TM) delivers data in seven spectral channels</LI>
</UL>

<P>TM-data are available in full scenes, quarter scenes and mini scenes.
</P>

<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Landsat information:</FONT></H2>

<TABLE BORDER=1 >
<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Landsat MSS</H2>
</TD>

<TD>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Landsat TM</H2>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD align=center><B>Ground resolution</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>80 m </P></CENTER>
</TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>30 m</P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD align=center><B>Scene size</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>183 x 183 km</P></CENTER>
</TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>183 x 183 km</P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD align=center><B>Spectral information</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>4 spectral channels</P></CENTER>
</TD>

<TD>
