<HEAD>
   <TITLE></TITLE>
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Romana Erlacher">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win16; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/ofd12b.gif">

<CENTER><P><A HREF="/ofd/hmofd_e.html"><IMG SRC="/images/ofd12.gif"></A></P></CENTER>
<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">SPOT</FONT></H1>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<P>The first<B> French satellite</B> SPOT-1 was launched in 1986 and operates at an
altitude of approx. 830 km. SPOT-2 followed in 1990 and SPOT-3 in 1993
, SPOT-4 is planned in 1997. SPOT-2 und 3 which are equipped with two optical
sensors, a multispectral (3 channels) and a panchromatic sensor (1 channel
- black/white). The sensors of both satellites can be switched so they can
reach a repetition time of up to 3 days for a specific area. SPOT 1 can
be activated at any time if needed.</P>

<P>Special characteristics of the French satellite: </P>

<UL>
<LI>the possibility of <B>programming</B> the satellite (decreasing costs
for large areas) </LI>

<LI><B>stereo-images</B> (two pictures in different angles taken at approximately
the same time - for digital terrain models)</LI>
</UL>

<P>SPOT offers so called SPOTView products, whereby SPOT Scenes are geo-corrected
and brought into a map-projection. This product is especially qualified
for the direct use in Geographical Information Systems. </P>

<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Spot information</FONT></H2>

