<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/ofd12b.gif">

<CENTER><P><A HREF="/ofd/hmofd_e.html"><IMG SRC="/images/ofd12.gif" ></A></P></CENTER>

<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Russian data- high resolution</FONT></H1>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<P><B>Optical cameras</B> on the <B>Russian space station MIR</B> provide
photographic images of the earth surface. The films are brought to earth
by the shuttle <B>&quot;SOYUZ&quot;</B>. The images can be delivered as
analog photographic products or scanned as digital data. The special characteristic
of these data is the high ground resolution. Black and white images as
well as colour images are available. <B>KFA 1000, MK 4 and KATE 200</B>
are recording with an overlap of 60 % and are therefore qualified for stereoanalysis
(digital terrain models).</P>

<P>Russian data are also available from the <b>COSMOS</b> satellites,
wich are equipped with the KVR 1000 camera. These satellites of the Russian
military generation is cruising at a height of 200 km and takes panchromatic
pictures of the Earth. The life time of a satellite is only 45 days due
to the limited fuel and film resources. Because of the military character
of the mission specific information about some aspects of the operation
of the satellite are not available.</P>

<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Russian data information:</FONT></H2>

