<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/ofd12b.gif">

<CENTER><P><A HREF="/ofd/hmofd_e.html"><IMG SRC="/images/ofd12.gif"></A>
</P></CENTER>

<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Resurs-01</FONT></H1>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<P>The <B>Russian Resurs-01 satellite</B> was launched in november 1994 
and is currently at a position of 678 km above the Earth. Data are available
since October 1995. This satellite ist already the third satellite of the
Resurs-01 mission, carrying the<B> multispectral camera MSU-SK</B>. The
aquisition of data directly from Russia has been sometimes difficult. For
the first time Russian data is received by a West European receiving station
in <B>Kiruna/Sweden</B>. From there the programming of the satellite is
also managed. This cooperation makes an easier and more reliable availability
of the data possible. With a ground resolution of 170 m the data of Resus-01
presents the golden mean between NOAA 1 km data and Landsat TM data (30
m) and is espacially suited for regional studies. The optimum revisit time
is <B>4 days</B>.</P>

<P>Images are mainly available from Europe, North America, South America,
North Africa and South East Asia.</P>

<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Resurs-01 information:</FONT></H2>

<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=1 >
<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Resurs-01</FONT></B></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><B>Ground resolution</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>170 m</P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><B>Scene size</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>600 x 600 km </P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><B>Spectral information</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>5 spectral channels</P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><B>Proposed maxim. scale</B></TD>

<TD>approx. 1:500 000</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
