<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/ofd12b.gif">

<CENTER><P><A HREF="/ofd/hmofd_e.html"><IMG SRC="/images/ofd12.gif"></A>
</P></CENTER>

<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">JERS-1</FONT></H1>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<P>The <B>Japanese Earth Resource Satellite (JERS) </B>was launched in
February 1992 and operates at a height of 568 km. It carries an <B>optical and a radar
</B>sensor. The revisit time is <B>44 days</B>. Each revisit guarantees
at least two consecutive coverages at mid-European latitudes, which presents
an interesting opportunity for temporal monitoring projects.</P>

<P>Besides the optical sensor JERS 1 is also carrying a SAR (Synthetic
Aperture Radar), which is actively sending out microwaves and recording
their reflection from the Earth surface. JERS 1 mainly covers Asia, Europe
and North America.</P>

<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Jers-1 information:</FONT></H2>

<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=1 >
