<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">ERS - European Remote Sensing Satellite</FONT></H1>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<P>The<B> European satellite ERS-1 </B>(developed by the European Space
Ageny - ESA) was launched in 1991 at an altitude of 780 km. The second
satellite <B>ERS-2</B> followed in 1995. In contrary to optical sensor
systems radar satellites actively send <B>microwaves</B> to the Earth and
record their reflection from the earth surface. Radarwaves <B>penetrate
the cloud cover</B> and are independent from sunlight. Especially for areas
with high cloud cover these data are an important additional information
source to optical sensors. The European radar satellite provides a repeat
circle of 35 days. </P>

<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">ERS information:</FONT></H2>

<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=1 >
<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>ERS</FONT></B></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
