<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">RADARSAT</FONT></H1>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<P>The<B> Canadian satellite</B> was launched in November 1995 and operates 
at an altitude
of 800 km. In contrary to optical sensor systems radar satellites actively
send <B>microwaves </B>to the earth an record their reflection from the
earth surface. Radarwaves penetrate the cloud cover and are independent
from sunlight. Especially for areas with high cloud cover these data are
an additionnal information source to optical sensors. The Canadian radar
satellite provides a repeat circle of<B> 24 days.</B></P>

<P>Radarsat provides images from <B>different incident angles</B> as well
as images with <B>different ground resolution and scene sizes</B>. A wide
range of image products is therefore available which are able to meet the
users specific needs.<B> Programming</B> of Radarsat is possible.</P>

<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Radarsat information</FONT></H2>

<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=1 WIDTH="50%" HEIGHT="10%" >
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="3%"></TD>

<TD WIDTH="20%">
<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Radarsat</FONT></B></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><B>Ground resolution</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>10 - 100 m</P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><B>Scene size</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER>50 x 50 km to <br>500 x 500 km</CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><B>Costs</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>from US$ 4000,-</P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><B>Quick-Look</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><P>no</P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><B>Data available on</B></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER>film, CD-ROM, CCT</CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Applications:</FONT></H2>

<UL>
<LI>Especially qualified for sea and ice-studies </LI>

<LI>Complementary to optical data for landuse and forestry applications
in areas with high cloud cover </LI>

<LI>Evaluation of digital terrain models (Interferometry)</LI>
</UL>

<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Limitations:</FONT></H2>

<UL>
<LI>Software for data processing and data evaluation. </LI>
</UL>

<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Special offers:</FONT></H2>

<UL>
<LI>Reductions are offered for monitoring (several number of scenes of
one area at different acquisitionn dates) and programming of several scenes.</LI>
</UL>

