and treatment.
<LI>Community prevention and education programs.
<LI>Local media advocacy campaigns.
<LI>Resource Centers for literature and audio-visual materials.
<LI>Presentations to raise community awareness at schools,
  businesses and community organizations.
<LI>Advocacy for alcoholics and other drug dependent persons and
  their families in local and state governments.
</UL>
<BR>
<TABLE BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="graphics/volun.gif" ALT="Volunteer to join the fight, 1-800-NCA-CALL" width=220 height=253></TD>
<TD>NCADD, which  does not accept funding from the alcoholic
  beverage or tobacco industries, relies on contributions from
  individuals, foundations and corporations for support. 
<I><UL> 
<LI>It costs $10,000 to print and distribute a pamphlet to
  alert pre-teens to the disturbing facts about alcohol. 
  
<LI>It costs $50,000 a year to operate the 24-hour HOPE Line,
  the critical and often only link between the alcoholic
  sufferer and help. 
  
<LI>It costs $100,000 to produce a video to help parents teach
  their children about the dangers of alcohol and other drugs.
</UL>
<B>You can join the fight by contributing your resources and
  time to the NCADD <A HREF="affildir.html">Affiliate</A> in your community or the
  national office.</B></I></TD>
</TABLE>
