<TITLE>NCADD - Publications List</TITLE>

<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="R. Coleman, Occasional Designs">
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<IMG SRC="graphics/pubban.gif" ALT="NCADD Publications" width=672 height=84>
<BR>
<H2>NCADD NEWSLETTERS/FAX SERVICE</H2>
<HR>
  <UL>
<LI><PRE>  The Alcoholism Report  
  
  Monthly newsletter reports on public policy news from
  Washington, DC.  $97 annual subscription fee.  To order,
  contact:  P.O. Box 11318, Birmingham, AL, 35202-1319,
  800/633-4931; fax 205/995-1588.
  </PRE>
<LI><PRE>  NCADD Amethyst
  
  Quarterly user-friendly information tool for the prevention
  and treatment of alcoholism and other drug addiction.  $50
  annual subscription fee.  To order, contact:  NCADD, 12 West
  21 Street, New York, NY, 10010, 212/206-6770; fax
  212/645-1690.
  </PRE>
<LI><PRE>  NCADD Amethyst "Plus"
  
  Special fax service includes advance notice of alcohol- and
  other drug-related national television programming and time-
  sensitive information about federal government activities
  for constituent action.  $50 annual subscription fee.  To
  order, contact:  NCADD, 12 West 21 Street, New York, NY,
  10010, 212/206-6770; fax 212/645-1690.
  </PRE>
</UL>
<HR>
  <H2><A HREF="factsdir.html">FACT SHEETS</A> </H2> 
<HR>
<PRE>
  $0.20   Alcohol-Related Birth Defects (Rev. 1994)
  $0.20   Alcoholism and Alcohol-Related Problems (Rev. 1995)
  $0.20   Use of Alcohol and Other Drugs Among Women (1994)
  $0.20   Alcohol and Other Drugs in the Workplace (1992)  
  $0.20   Youth and Alcohol (Rev. 1996)
  </PRE>
<HR>
  <H2>BROCHURES</H2>
<HR>
<PRE>  GENERAL

  $0.50   The Disease of Alcoholism.  Gives a brief
          historical overview of the disease definition of  
          alcoholism, and explains how alcoholism develops
          and how it can be prevented.  (1992) 
  
  $0.50   What Are the Signs of Alcoholism?  The NCADD
          Self-Test.  Our classic test, which asks 26  
          yes/no questions to help determine if you or
          someone you know needs to find out more about
          alcoholism. (Rev. 1990)
  
  $0.50   What Can You Do About Someone Else's Drinking?  A
          helpful guide for anyone involved in a
          relationship with someone who may be an alcoholic. 
          (Rev. 1990)

  PREVENTION MATERIAL FOR <A HREF="pardir.html">PARENTS</A> 
  
  $1.00   <A HREF="parent1.html">What Should I Tell My Child About Drinking?</A> 
          Comprehensive guide offers advice for various   
          stages of a child's development and features a
          series of "teachable moments" that give parents a
          structured opportunity to sit down with their
          child and discuss alcohol.  (1996)
          <I>Companion video also available.  See below. </I>


  PREVENTION MATERIALS FOR <A HREF="youdir.html">YOUTH</A>
  
  $0.50   Kids Talk To Kids About Alcohol.  Uses actual
          drawings and quotes from children ages 9 to 11  to
          stimulate thought and discussion.  (1992)
  
  $0.50   Wine Coolers?  NOT!  A colorful look at a beverage
          many teenagers don't even know contains alcohol.
          (1992)
  
  $0.50   <A HREF="youth.html">Who's Got the Power?  You . . . Or Drugs?</A> 
          Straight talk--in their own words--for adolescent 
          guys and girls, plus important health information,
          all in day-glo colors.  (1992)
  
  $0.50   Girls!  Straight Talk About Drinking and Drugs. 
          Gender-specific information for teen girls vividly
          conveyed in language they use and understand.
          (1993)
  
  $0.50   Quien Tiene el Poder, el Alcohol O Tu?
          Culturally appropriate straight talk from teens
          about alcohol and other drugs, this time in
          Spanish and even brighter colors.  (1993)
  
<HR>
<H2>POSTERS</H2>
<HR>

  $1.00   Don't Let Drinking Take Your Power Away.  Part of
          our "Prevention Series for Youth," this poster
          targets teen girls with a dramatic photograph. 
          Printed both sides in English and Spanish.
          Four-color, 15 1/2" x 22 1/2."  (1992)
  
  $1.00   Alcohol:  A Powerful Drug.  Developed with the
          Weekly Reader Corporation, this double-sided  
          poster communicates health information by showing
          the effects of alcohol on various organs of the
          human body, and a prevention message for teens by
          asking "Sure You Want to Be One of the Pack?" 
          Four-color, 21" x 30" (1994)
 </PRE> 
<HR>
  <H2>VIDEO</H2>
<HR>

<PRE> 
  $59.99   What Should I Tell My Child About Drinking?
           Hosted by Meryl Streep, this two-part video will help
           parents and other caregivers improve their
           communication skills about alcohol.  Package includes
           companion brochure (see above) and facilitator's guide.
           VHS, 46 minutes, color.  (1996)

</PRE> 
<HR>
  <H2>ORDERING INFORMATION</H2>
  <HR>
  Except where otherwise indicated, please call <B>800/NCA-CALL</B>
  to receive an order form.<BR>
