<HEAD>
<TITLE>NIREX ENVIRONMENTAL POLICY</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="device2.jpg">
<P><IMG SRC="nirsmlogt.gif" ALIGN="TOP"></P>
<HR>
<H3><I>Company Mission Statement</I></H3>
<P><CITE>To provide a safe, environmentally sound and efficient service to
dispose of the nation's intermediate and some low-level radioactive waste.</CITE></P>
<H4>PREFACE BY THE CHAIRMAN</H4>
<P>Nirex is charged with the important task of providing and managing the
national repository for the disposal of intermediate and some low-level
radioactive waste. In undertaking this task &#150; which involves geological
investigations, repository construction, operation and closure &#150; we must
have regard to the environmental impacts attaching to each stage. To that end we
set ourselves high standards of environmental care to ensure that any adverse
environmental impacts of our work are kept to a minimum.</P>
<P>The Company recognises and accepts the concept of 'sustainable development'.
A widely-quoted definition of this concept is 'development that meets the needs
of the present without compromising the ability of future generations to meet
their own needs' (Ref. Cm2426). We must therefore all aim to ensure that our
actions are compatible with this goal.</P>
<P>The Board of Directors attaches great importance to this. An integral part
of the Company's task is to ensure that its activities, now and in the future,
are environmentally sound. Everyone working on behalf of the Company needs to
put this Environmental Policy into effect by:</P>
<UL>
<LI> conscientiously implementing the Company's Environmental Management
System;
</LI>
<LI> following Company Management Procedures and Instructions designed to
control environmental impacts; and
</LI>
<LI> monitoring performance against the Environmental Policy.
</LI></UL>
<P>I am confident that together we can ensure that Nirex will continue to
achieve high standards of environmental performance.</P><IMG
SRC="sign.gif" WIDTH="350" HEIGHT="87">
<P>Sir Richard Morris CBE, FEng</P>
<P>Chairman</P>
<P>1 November 1996, Issue 2.</P>
<P></P>
<H3>NIREX ENVIRONMENTAL POLICY</H3>
<P>[1] Nirex is committed to ensuring that high standards of environmental
performance are embodied in all activities for which the Company is responsible.</P>
<P>[2] The Company will act at all times in accordance with high standards of
environmental protection. </P>
<P>[3] The Company will provide appropriate training to its employees in
relation to their responsibilities for the management of environmental impacts.</P>
<P>[4] The Company will comply with all relevant environmental legislation.</P>
<P>[5] The Company will encourage its suppliers and contractors to pursue good
environmental practice.</P>
<P>[6] The Company will maintain a register of environmental effects stemming
from its current activities and a register of consents it obtains in order to
operate its business and facilities.</P>
<P>[7] The Company has a commitment to seek continual improvement in its
environmental performance and will develop and improve operations and methods of
work at its sites to reduce the production of waste and discharges to water, air
and land.</P>
<P>[8] The Company will monitor progress, report regularly on its environmental
performance and set targets for improvement. </P>
<P>[9] The Technical and Engineering Director will regularly review the
operation of this policy and the Board of Directors will receive regular reports
on its effectiveness.</P>
<H4>IMPLEMENTATION</H4>
<P>[10] Effective implementation of this policy requires the participation and
support of all employees who are responsible for achieving high standards of
environmental performance.</P>
<P>[11] The Company will institute a system of environmental management
designed to:</P>
<P>(a) assess likely environmental impacts arising from its activities;</P>
<P>(b) measure, monitor and control the environmental impacts of its
activities.</P>
<P>[12] The Environmental Management System will be implemented through
documented management procedures and instructions designed to control
environmental impacts. The procedures and instructions will define
responsibilities.</P>
<P>[13] As part of the Environmental Management System the Company will
maintain and regularly update:</P>
<P>(a) a Register of the environmental effects of its activities;</P>
<P>(b) a Register of the consents it is required to obtain for emissions to
land, air and water.</P>
<P>[14] Environmental effects of the Company's activities will be monitored
closely in order to:</P>
<P>(a) provide information on overall environmental impacts; </P>
<P>(b) provide guidance on priority areas for action;</P>
<P>(c) highlight trends in environmental impacts and,</P>
<P>(d) help set targets to improve environmental performance.</P>
<P>[15] Information on the environmental impacts of the Company's current
activities and progress towards targets to improve environmental performance
will be made available to the public through the publication of Environmental
Reports.</P>
<H4>AUDIT AND REVIEW</H4>
<P>[16] The Company will audit its performance against the Environmental Policy
to a programme approved annually by the Board.</P>
<P>[17] Environmental audits will be undertaken by employees who have received
appropriate training. Audits will be subject to review by external specialists,
whose conclusions will be included in Environmental Reports.</P>
<P>[18] To assist the Board in ensuring that the Environmental Policy remains
relevant to the Company's activities, the Board has nominated the Technical and
Engineering Director to:</P>
<P>(a) be responsible for the successful implementation of the Environmental
Policy and audit/review of environmental performance;</P>
<P>(b) establish an Environmental Management Committee, chaired by the
Technical and Engineering Director, to receive all audit and review reports and
to report to the Board on    the effectiveness of and revisions to the Policy;
and,</P>
<P>(c) appoint to that committee an independent specialist advisor.</P>
<P>For further information or copies of this policy statement contact: </P>
<P>United Kingdom Nirex Limited</P>
