<HR>
<H3>BNFL Man Joins Nirex Board</H3>
<P><B>George Beveridge</B>, BNFL's Director of Waste Retrieval and
Commissioning has been appointed to the Board of  Nirex.</P>
<P>31-year-old Mr Beveridge, who is BNFL's youngest ever director, has been
nominated by the Company to replace Ken Jackson, the former Engineering Group
Director.</P>
<P>The other members of the16-strong Nirex Board are:</P>
<P><B>Sir Richard Morris</B><BR>Chairman, Nirex</P>
<P><B>Michael Folger</B><BR>Chief Executive, Nirex</P>
<P><B>Chris Murray</B><BR>Finance and Corporate Services Director, Nirex</P>
<P><B>The Lord Cavendish of Furness </B></P>
<P><B>Brian George</B><BR>Associate Director, General Electric Company plc
and Chief Executive of GEC Marine Ltd</P>
<P><B>Dennis Joynson</B><BR>Executive Director, Liabilities, Waste Management
and Decommissioning for Magnox Electric plc</P>
<P><B>Jean Macdonald</B><BR>Company Secretary, Scottish Nuclear Ltd and Head
of Legal Services at British Energy plc</P>
<P><B>Roy Nelson</B><BR>Director, Decommissioning and Radioactive Waste
Management Operations at UKAEA Government Division</P>
<P><B>Stephen Ogle</B><BR>Executive Director, Finance and Commercial of
Magnox Electric plc</P>
<P><B>Sir Ronald Oxburgh</B><BR>Rector of Imperial College of Science,
Technology and Medicine</P>
<P><B>Derek Pooley</B><BR>Chief Executive of the UKAEA</P>
<P><B>Grahame Smith</B><BR>Director, Magnox Group and Head of Sellafield Site
at British Nuclear Fuels plc</P>
<P><B>Neil Stewart</B><BR>Finance and Commercial Director at Scottish Nuclear
Ltd</P>
