<TITLE>Nirex Restarts Drilling Programme - NX39-96</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<P><IMG SRC="images/nirsmlog.gif" ALT="Nirex logo" ALIGN="TOP"></P>
<HR>
<H3>Nirex Restarts Drilling Programme</H3>
<P>Nirex restarts its deep drilling programme on Monday (December 8) after a
break of almost two years, with the creation of 15-20 jobs.</P>
<P>Drilling operations on Borehole 16 at Seascale How will run for
approximately 12 weeks. </P>
<P>Nirex is assessing the suitability of Longlands Farm near Sellafield as a
potential site for a deep repository for intermediate and some low-level
radioactive waste.</P>
<P>The Company has drilled 27 deep boreholes since 1990 as part of  its
long-term assessment of the movement of water through the rocks beneath the
site.</P>
<P>Nirex will also be completing a borehole at Longlands Farm, which was left
unfinished in 1995 to avoid disrupting sensitive hydrogeological monitoring
experiments at the site.  This will be followed next spring by drilling Borehole
15 - near the Blackbeck Bridge Inn, east of the BNFL Sellafield site.</P>
<P><B><U>NOTE TO NEWSDESKS</U></B>: </P>
<P><B>If you would like to film or take photographs at the site or on the rig
platform, please contact us as below.   For safety reasons, your staff will need
the appropriate headgear and footwear so their shoe size will be needed.</B></P>
<P><CITE>NX 39/96  5th December 1996</CITE></P>
