<HEAD>
<META HTTP-EQUIV="Content-Type" CONTENT="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1">
<TITLE>Design Concepts for Potential Repository</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.04z"></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFFFF">
<P><IMG SRC="images/nirsmlog.gif" ALT="Nirex logo" ALIGN="TOP"></P>
<HR>
<H3>Design Concepts for Potential Repository</H3>
<P>Nirex has started a consultation programme on new engineering design
concepts for a potential repository for the disposal of radioactive waste at
Longlands Farm near Sellafield, should the site prove suitable.
</P>
<P>Since the Company last presented its thinking in 1991, the volume of waste
for disposal has dropped to about one tenth of the 2 million cubic metres
originally envisaged.
</P>
<P>Technical and Engineering Director, Colin Bayliss, said: &quot;In addition
to the shift in the volume of waste since 1991, we have also announced our plans
to construct a Rock Laboratory (or 'Rock Characterisation Facility') to confirm
whether the site is suitable. 
</P>
<P>&quot;These two factors obviously impinge upon the design and construction
options for any repository. On Monday we presented three outline concepts for
consultation to the Gosforth/Nirex Technical Liaison Meeting.&quot;
</P>
<P>The earliest construction of a repository could begin is 2004 - and then
only if the RCFscience work demonstrates the suitability of the site.
Considerable development work on design will need to be undertaken between now
and then. Any application to construct a repository will be the subject of a
major public inquiry.
</P>
<P>Radioactive waste would be transported to the repository via BNFL's
Sellafield site either by twin drifts (tunnels), a single drift, or a dual-use
drift which could be used for both emplacing waste and removing rock spoil.
</P>
<P>Dr Bayliss added: &quot;Each of these three concepts has different
implications as regards environmental impact and cost. We are meeting local
people to get their views.
</P>
<P>&quot;Our 1991 designs took account of local views and we will, wherever
possible, continue to respect those views.&quot; 
</P>
<P><CITE>NX 36/96  19th November 1996  </CITE></P>
<P><I>Media Enquiries:</I>
</P>
<P>Taryn Rock:	     019467 24880 (office)    0385 336091 (mobile)    01900
827174 (home)
</P>
<P>Nigel Monckton:   019467 24885 (office)    0836 387584 (mobile)    01900
817045 (home)  
</P>
