<HEAD>
<TITLE>Companies Invited to Tender for Science Contract. NX28/96</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<P><IMG SRC="images/nirsmlog.gif" ALT="Nirex logo" ALIGN="TOP"></P>
<HR>
<H3>Companies Invited to Tender for Science Contract</H3>
<P>Nirex, the radioactive waste disposal company, has issued invitations to
tender for the Science Design Contract associated with the first stage of a Rock
Laboratory ( or &quot;Rock Characterisation Facility&quot;) at Longlands Farm,
near Sellafield in West Cumbria, subject to the Company obtaining planning
permission for the development.</P>
<P>The winning contractor will produce detailed designs and plans for
scientific measurements which will be taken during the shaft-sinking phase.</P>
<P>Nirex will subsequently award a second contract - the Science Execution
Contract - to carry out detailed scientific measurements which are needed once
shaft-sinking begins. These measurements will be carried out throughout
shaft-sinking in a programme integrated with the construction works.</P>
<P>The invitation to tender for the construction work for Phase I of the Rock
Laboratory, which comprises the sinking of two 5m diameter shafts vertically to
a depth of between 650m and 900rn bOD, connected at the bottom by a tunnel, was
issued on 26 July 1996.</P>
<P>Dr David Mellor, RCF Science Manager, said: &quot;It is important that we
invite tenders now, especially for the detailed design elements of the work,
because it takes many months to put major contracts such as these in place. This
preparation will ensure that Nirex is in a position to move forward in a timely
way if the Secretary of State gives planning permission for the Rock Laboratory.&quot;</P>
<P>Four consortia have been invited to tender. They are:</P>
<UL>
<LI> Entec-Hyder &amp; Associates (Entec UK Ltd, Hyder Consulting Ltd)
</LI>
<LI> GIGA (GeoScience Ltd, Intera, Sir Alexander Gibb)
</LI>
<LI> SCICON (Ove Arup &amp; Partners, Rock Mechanics Technology, CSM 
Associates Ltd, Graham Daws Associates, Taywood Engineering)
</LI>
<LI> SAIC (Science Applications International Corporation, Lawrence Berkeley
National Laboratory)
</LI></UL>
<P>The tender return date is 29 November 1996. Both the Shaft-Sinking and the
Science Design contracts will be awarded in the New Year.</P>
<P>A public inquiry into Nirex proposals for a Rock Laboratory ended on 1
February 1996 and the Inspector stated his intention to report by the end of
October. The inquiry report will be submitted to the Secretary of State for the
Environment for a decision.</P>
<P><BR><BR></P>
<P><CITE>NX 28/96 10th October 1996</CITE></P>
<P><I>Media Enquiries:</I>
</P>
<P>Taryn Rock:	     019467 24880 (office)    0385 336091 (mobile)    01900
827174 (home)
</P>
<P>Nigel Monckton:   019467 24885 (office)    0836 387584 (mobile)    01900
817045 (home)  
</P>
