<HEAD>
<TITLE>Significant Year for Nirex, says Annual Report. NX20/96</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<P><IMG SRC="images/nirsmlog.gif" ALT="Nirex logo" ALIGN="TOP"></P>
<HR>
<H3>Significant Year for Nirex, says Annual Report</H3>
<P>Nirex has published its annual report for 1995/96, which was a &quot;significant&quot;
year for the Company according to its Chairman, Sir Richard Morris.</P>
<P>It was notable, he says, for both publication of the final conclusions of
the Government's Review of Radioactive Waste Management Policy and completion of
the planning inquiry into the Company's application to build a 'Rock Laboratory'
or Rock Characterisation Facility, at Longlands Farm near Sellafield.</P>
<P>Sir Richard says the 66-day public inquiry provided the opportunity for a
thorough and<B> </B>open review of the Company's programme. He adds: &quot;The
Company now looks forward to an early and favourable decision by the Secretary
of State for the Environment so that work on the construction of the RCF can
begin, which we hope can be early in 1997&quot;.</P>
<P>Nirex is also looking forward to the formation of a joint consultation
committee, a concept agreed with Cumbria County Council during the year. It will
review in an open way the progress of the Nirex programme, including results
from the site characterisation work at Sellafield.</P>
<P>Says Sir Richard: &quot;During the year we have continued to lay great
emphasis on the importance of liaison with local communities. to keep people
fully apprised of our programme. We respect the views of those who, for whatever
reason, oppose the disposal of radioactive waste.<I> </I>However, while we
accept that we shall not gain total acceptance for our programme, we believe a
continuing dialogue is essential.&quot;</P>
<P>Final conclusions of the Government's Review of Radioactive Waste Management
Policy were announced in July 1995. They reaffirmed the policy of deep disposal
rather than indefinite storage of intermediate level wastes, and saw no
advantage in delaying construction of a repository.</P>
<P>&quot;This has given us a clear framework within which we can manage our
long-term task&quot; says Sir Richard.</P>
<P><CITE>NX  20/96 12th August 1996</CITE></P>
