Content-type: text/html
Content-length: 902
Last-modified: Tue, 02 Apr 1996 10:05:14 GMT
</DOCHDR>
<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Nirex : The Company</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF"><IMG
SRC="images/nirsmlog.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<HR>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">Nirex is financed by organisations which will eventually
dispose of their wastes in the repository: British Nuclear Fuels plc; Nuclear
Electric plc; UK Atomic Energy Authority, Scottish Nuclear Ltd and the Ministry
of Defence (MoD).  All except the MoD hold ordinary shares in Nirex and in
addition the Secretary of State for Trade and Industry has a special share. 
Nirex was formed as an executive body in 1982 and incorporated as a limited
company - United Kingdom Nirex Limited - in 1985.</P>
<P> Nirex  staff operate from Greengarth Hall, Holmrook, West Cumbria and
Harwell, Didcot, Oxfordshire.</P>
<P><A HREF="nirfx3.htm">Source of the radioactive
waste.</A></P>
