<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Radioactive Waste Exists</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<IMG SRC="images/nirsmlog.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<HR>
<H3>Radioactive waste exists now</H3>
<P><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" SRC="images/pic10.gif" HSPACE="15" HEIGHT="150">The
equivalent of some 60,000 cubic metres of intermediate-level radioactive waste
exists today.  <BR><BR>That's about enough to cover a football pitch to a
depth of some 7 metres.  It is currently held on the surface at nuclear power
stations and other facilities.  
<BR><BR>About the same quantity again will be generated by 2010. 
<BR CLEAR="YES"><BR>Nirex's task is to find a permanent solution for these
wastes.  That solution is disposal in chambers built in rock deep underground.</P>
<P><A HREF="nirfx5.htm">Why bury the waste?</A></P>
<P><A HREF="nirfxall.htm">Return to section menu</A></P></BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT05-B15-178</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA047-000826-B015-188</DOCOLDNO>
