<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The planning process</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC="images/nirsmlog.gif" ALIGN="TOP">
<HR>
<H3>The planning process</H3>
<P>Nirex applied for planning permission for the Rock Lab and this was refused
by Cumbria County Council.  Nirex appealed to the Secretary of State for the
Environment against the decision and a Public Inquiry into the application has
now been held. The Secretary of State's decision is expected in 1997.  </P>
<P>Although the Rock Lab is in the same area as the proposed repository, no
part of it could be re-used for repository purposes unless entirely separate
planning permission is given.  It is Nirex's view that research associated with
sinking the Rock Lab shafts down into the BVG will be needed for a decision on
whether to seek planning permission for a repository.  An application to develop
a repository would be considered at a full Public Inquiry at which all the
evidence will be carefully examined by technical and legal experts and the
safety regulatory bodies would give their views.  Naturally, there is much
uncertainty in a long-term programme such as this one - not least from the Town
and Country Planning Act procedures applying at various stages.  Depending on
these and other factors, Nirex aims to bring a repository into operation by
2012. 
</P>
<P>Throughout its programme, Nirex is committed to consultation and keeping the
public informed.</P>

