<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Safety and Science behind the repository</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF"><IMG
SRC="images/nirsmlog.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Safety">Safety and science behind the repository</A></H3>
<P></P>
<P>It would be pretty easy to provide a repository system that would safe for
100, 200 or even 300 years - the steel drums containing the radioactive waste
alone should see to that.  But Nirex's task is much bigger - the repository will
have to meet some of the most stringent safety requirements in the world; the
target is that the annual risk to an individual from a repository will not
exceed one in a million.  (This is about 1 per cent of the risk theoretically
implied by average natural background radiation in the UK.) </P>
<P><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" SRC="images/pic33.gif" HSPACE="15" HEIGHT="150"><CITE>Experiments
have been carried out for some years at a disused quarry in Cornwall to measure
how water moves through hard rock.</CITE></P>
<P><BR CLEAR="LEFT">
<BR></P>
<P>This applies not just for now but until the radioactivity fades over tens of
thousands of years, by which time the drums will have corroded.  Water will seep
through the repository.  This could bring radioactivity back to the surface.
</P>
<P ALIGN="RIGHT"><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" SRC="images/pic13.gif" HSPACE="15" HEIGHT="150"><CITE>Tests
will be carried out underground, such as at the Rock Lab in Canada (left)</CITE></P>
<P ALIGN="RIGHT"><IMG
ALIGN="RIGHT" SRC="images/pic21.gif" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="10" HEIGHT="150"><CITE>and
at Grimsel in Switzerland (right).</CITE></P>
<P><BR><BR CLEAR="RIGHT"><BR CLEAR="LEFT">Climate too can change.  Despite
the possibility of global warming, an Ice Age is predicted to return to Cumbria
within 100,000 years.  Glaciers would scour the Earth's surface.  All of these
factors have to be taken into account in safety calculations. Nirex has a
substantial research programme using some of the most advanced computer
techniques to address these complex issues in a comprehensive demonstration of
repository safety.  
</P>
<P><A HREF="nirfx10.htm">Monitoring and retrieving the
waste</A></P>
<P><A HREF="nirfxall.htm">Return to section 
menu</A></P>
