<P><B>Rail Access</B></P>
<P>3.12 There  is  no rail  connection  from  the Cumbria  Coast  Line  to  the
 Surface Site  and the topography between the Cumbrian Coast Line and the
Surface Site would render a direct connection impracticable.</P>
<P>3.13 The dominant materials movement associated with RCF construction is the
removal of  the spoil from the shafts and galleries. However, the spoil will
remain on the Surface Site with the possible exception of some Borrowdale
Volcanic Group ('BVG') rock which may be removed off site for testing purposes.</P>
<P>3.14 There is no economic justification for the use of rail deliveries for
the relatively small quantities and variable mix of materials required for RCF
construction. The highest materials flows occur for only a short duration.</P>
