<P><BR><BR><A NAME="Table7.1"></A><CITE>TABLE 7.1: RCF PLANNING APPLICATION
CONSULTATIONS - SUMMARY OF RESPONSES ON TRAFFIC AND HIGHWAYS ISSUES</CITE></P>
<TABLE BORDER="BORDER">
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1"><B>CONSULTEE<BR>(Reference/Page No.)</B></FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1"><B>RESPONSE SUMMARY</B></FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1"><B>COMMENT</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD ROWSPAN="6"><FONT SIZE="-1">Gosforth Parish Council<BR>Ref 5/Pages
16/17/18</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">Extra work should be carried out along...A595...</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">DOT does no objection to the development; no extra work on
the A595 is required due to the development.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">The access to Longlands should be from Sellafield...</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">There would be operational and logistical problems to this
and a new road from Sellafield to Longlands Farm is not needed to accommodate
the low traffic flows generated by the development.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">use of the railway line for materials...</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">The low volume and diversity of construction materials
make use of the rail access to Sellafield inappropriate.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">...feasibility study for the railway from Carnforth to
Carlisle</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">Not warranted by RCF construction.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">The state of the rail links are just reason for a full
inquiry...</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">Rationale not justified.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">...help in provision of car parking...</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">Nirex already provides financial assistance towards the
provision of free car parking in Gosforth and requests to continue this
arrangement will be given consideration.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">St Bridget Beckermet Parish Council<BR>Ref 5/Page 18</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">...A595 is already overburdened</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">Spare capacity exists on the A595(T). The change in
traffic flow due to the RCF is small and within natural traffic growth rate over
the life of the RCF.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">Lamplugh Parish Council<BR>Ref 5/Page 18</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">...road network inadequate...development...would lead to a
worsening of the situation.</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">Analysis shows road network can accommodate the small
change in flows for the life of the RCF.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">The Local Council of Millom Without<BR>Ref 5/Page 18</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">Are concerned at the impact of heavy goods vehicles.
...spoil should not be routed to South Cumbria.</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">The environmental effects of the extra volume of HGVs
generated by the development will be minimal. Most spoil will be disposed of on
site.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">Millom Town Council<BR>Ref 5/Page 18</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">...consider roads are not suitable for present
requirements.</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="-1">Analysis shows road network can accommodate the small
change in flows for the life of the RCF.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD COLSPAN="3"><FONT SIZE="-1"><B>STATUTORY AGENCIES</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
