<P>4.8 The 1980s were a period of substantial contraction in manufacturing
employment and this was evident in West Cumbria, as it was in the UK as a whole.
Table 4.4 shows the percentage changes in employment in those industries which
can be taken to comprise a significant part of the 'economic base' of West
Cumbria, this comprising manufacturing sectors, primary industries, extraction
industries and nuclear fuel production. The Standard Industrial Classification
(SIC) is a system used by the Central Statistical Office to classify employment
by activity.</P>
