<P>5.7 Over the entire period 1996-2008, the RCF's direct labour requirements
will be an annual average of 97, with a peak requirement of 185 person years of
direct employment in 1999 (see <A HREF="#Table5.3">Table 5.3</A>). Both figures
are substantially below the employment losses in BNFL direct and contractor
employment since 1991 (see
<A HREF="#Table4.3">Table 4.3</A>).</P>
<P><B>Indirect/Induced Employment</B></P>
<P>5.8 It is not possible in the advance of a development, and particularly a
new form of development such as the RCF, to be certain as to the number of
indirect and induced jobs which would be associated with any level of direct
employment. However, it is possible to estimate the likely number of
indirect/induced jobs based on the employment multipliers calculated by ex-post
facto studies of other developments.</P>
<P>5.9 In the Environmental Statement we reviewed a range of employment
multipliers based on studies of Hinkley Point, Dounreay and Torness and we
reproduce Table 3.3.8 from the Environmental Statement [COR/101](10) as Table
5.2 below.</P>
