<TD>5</TD></TR></TABLE>
<P>5.23 Subsequent to the Environmental Statement I have reviewed the likely
extent of local recruitment in the light of Nirex experience with the current
borehole programme. As regards contractor labour, 59% of the March 1995 labour
force was locally recruited, the percentage in this category rising steadily
from 19% at the start of the site characterisation programme. As to future
contractor activities associated with the RCF, the estimates provided by Nirex
suggest that local recruitment may vary substantially depending on the
particular activity involved.</P>
<P>5.24 The local labour market impact will obviously vary with the level of
associated employment which shows considerable fluctuation over the period to
2008 (see <A HREF="#Table5.3">Table 5.3</A>). However, the essential point
remains that given the level of direct employment, variations in the scale of
local recruitment would not cause significant local labour market difficulties.</P>
